# Implementation Plan - Phase 1 Farmer Mobile App

The goal of this plan is to design and implement a visually stunning, highly interactive Flutter mobile app for **Phase 1 (Farmer Mobile)**. 

To answer the core question: **"Can I monitor and control my farm from my phone?"** without requiring complex hardware setup, the app will include a local state engine that simulates real-time monitoring and control. Tapping "Start Irrigation" will immediately transition the app state, update the dashboard telemetry, trigger notifications, and reflect running zone details on the field detail page.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Self-Contained Architecture vs. Multi-File modularity**:
> We propose organizing the entire app in `lib/main.dart` or a minimal structure (`lib/main.dart` with auxiliary state/model files). Putting everything in a single, well-structured file is highly recommended for Phase 1 as it facilitates zero-setup execution, makes previews flawless, and avoids nested importing issues. We will structure it with clearly commented sections (Models, State, Theme, Screens, Custom Widgets).
>
> **Interactive State Engine**:
> To make the app "live," we will build a `FarmerAppState` class (using `ChangeNotifier` and `Provider` or standard Flutter state management) which stores:
> - User Info & Authentication state (Login, Forgot Password, OTP).
> - Active fields (North Farm, South Farm, East Farm) and their zones.
> - Current running zone, remaining time (counting down in real-time), and simulated values (flow rate, moisture %, tank level %).
> - Irrigation Schedules (create/edit/delete/pause).
> - Support Tickets (create/list).
> - Custom Alerts & Notifications list.

